      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Modern historians view the UN's effectiveness in preventing major wars in the 21st century as a mixed and often frustrating picture. While the Security Council has prevented some immediate large-scale conflicts from escalating into world wars, its inherent structure often leads to paralysis due to veto power among permanent members. Therefore, the UN is more often seen as a necessary forum for diplomacy and humanitarian aid, rather than a guaranteed guarantor against large-scale conflict.",
