      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Supporters argue that the veto is necessary to ensure that the UN does not authorize military action that would lead to a wider global conflict involving the great powers themselves. They contend that without a veto, powerful nations would simply ignore the UN anyway, making the organization irrelevant. Essentially, the argument is that the veto prevents the UN from becoming a tool of one dominant global hegemon.",
      "source": "target",
